# 5. 決意を新たに

Tsukasa: Thank you very much for agreeing to work with me on those things, Mr. Kijima!
Tsukasa: On top of that fight, you even stayed to coach me as I practiced on my own. I really appreciate the help.
Kijima: Not a problem! I understand exactly how you feel since I also want to do everything I can to put on a great show.
Kijima: Plus, we're both playing leads this time around, so we'll need to work in perfect sync.
Tsukasa: Very true... “Ishin-den”, the tale of two brothers separated at a young age who end up facing off as supporters of the new government and old shogunate.
Tsukasa: The climax involves an epic sword fight that will likely make or break the entire show. I'm incredibly excited about that scene!
Tsukasa: However...
Tsukasa: I still get the feeling that we can do more to make it even better...
Kijima: I see...
Tsukasa: I'm sorry... I wish I could be more specific.
Kijima: No, you don't need to apologize. It's important to keep searching for new ideas!
Kijima: That being said... You have to find the answer you're looking for on your own.
Kijima: And when you do, I have a feeling that you're going to grow more than you have until now.
Tsukasa: ...! More than I have until now...?
Tsukasa: Okay... I, Tsukasa Tenma, promise to find the answer!
Kijima: Hah hah hah! That's what I like to hear!
Kijima: Come to think of it, Tenma, have you replied to that message already?
Tsukasa: What message?
Kijima: The one you received while we were practicing. You said it was from your old friends.
Kijima: You started practicing on your own right after that, so I was wondering if you'd replied already.
Tsukasa: No, you're right...! I'd become so focused on practicing that I completely forgot...!
Tsukasa: I'll reply right now!
Kijima: Ah, I'm glad that you remembered!
Kijima: Still, you must all be pretty close to keep in contact like this after disbanding your troupe...
Tsukasa: Yes, well...
Tsukasa: The truth is, part of why I decided to go train overseas is because one of them inspired me...
Kijima: Really?
Tsukasa: Yes. I received word the other day that he will be joining a top-level troupe in the United States as he pursues his dream.
Tsukasa: And I felt that I couldn't let him hog all the glory.
Tsukasa: I know that I still need a lot of work, and that it's far too soon for me to go train abroad. But...
Tsukasa: I don't want to sit idly by as my friends move forward towards their dreams... Chiefly because I am the troupe leader of Wonderlands×Showtime!
Tsukasa: I have to be an example by fulfilling my dream and becoming a star who makes the whole world smile!
Kijima: I see... I like that. It's very you, Tenma.
Kijima: You're always heading straight towards your dream!
Kijima: So, keep running. Go become a big star!
Tsukasa: Mr. Kijima...
Tsukasa: Thank you! I will!
???: I'm sure you can. Aren't you a future star that will bring joy to everyone?
Tsukasa: (Who said that just now...?)
Tsukasa: (I have no idea, but it felt like they were trying to give me words of encouragement...)
Tsukasa: (This is it. My last show...)
Tsukasa: (I have to do my best to make sure I don't fall behind them...!)
Rokuro: “No, what are you doing here...?!”
Rokuro: “I gave you your chance to flee!”
Kansuke: “...!”
Tsukasa: (Okay, my timing was perfect! Next, we'll go from our swords being locked to a series of parries.)
Audience: Wow! Did you see that guy's wall jump...?!
Tsukasa: (He's improvising...! Okay, I'll get pushed back here, and take up a defensive posture.)
Kansuke: “Grr...!”
Kansuke: “R-Rokuro...!”
Audience: Wow, this scene's so amazing...!
Tsukasa: (The audience seems to really be enjoying this. Alright, next, I'll...)
Mikazukigumi Member C: No, I should be the one apologizing... I wasn't expecting you to throw in a spin there.
Tsukasa: (But this is Mr. Kijima's time to shine.)
Tsukasa: (I should just do precisely what we practiced!)
Kansuke: “Even so... Even so, I will choose this path...!”
Rokuro: “I see...”
Rokuro: “Then, we have no choice but to fight. Even if you are the only family I have left...!”
Kansuke: “Rokuro, I...”
Kansuke: “I regret nothing. I know we chose to go down different paths, but...”
Rokuro: “Yes, I also regret nothing. That is why...”
Rokuro: “I must be the one who ends you.”
Kansuke: “Yes, please do...”
Audience: I wasn't expecting it to end that way at all...! I mean, it started out kinda like a comedy...
Audience: That was so good! I didn't know Mikazukigumi could put on shows that make your heart ache like that...
Kijima: Hah hah hah! I think the crowd liked what they saw!
Tsukasa: That was the loudest applause we've heard...!
Tsukasa: Even until the very last second, I kept learning from you. The audience really loved the way you improvised back there!
Kijima: And you did a good job of reacting, Tenma!
Kijima: Tenma...
Kijima: Thank you for being with us until today. You've had a huge impact on this troupe. Myself included.
Kijima: You might face some tough challenges when you set out into the world, but I'm sure you'll find a way to overcome all of them!
Kijima: I'll be looking forward to the day you become a star.
Tsukasa: Thank you...!
Tsukasa: I'm going to treasure every moment I spent training with everyone here at Mikazukigumi.
Tsukasa: You all encouraged me to chase after my dream. So, to make the most of what you've given me...
Tsukasa: I will make my dream come true.
Tsukasa: Because I'm a future star!
Kijima: Good!
Kijima: Move forward with your head held high! Go make your dream come true!
Mikazukigumi Staff Member: Mr. Kijima! The venue staff said they'd all like to thank you.
Kijima: Oh, okay! I'll head right over. We'll talk again later, Tenma!
Tsukasa: Okay!
Kijima: ...
Kijima: (I wasn't able to draw out everything he had...)
Tsukasa: (The way I moved on stage, including during that fight... I felt that I performed better than during practice.)
Tsukasa: (But...)
Tsukasa: (But this is Mr. Kijima's time to shine.)
Tsukasa: (I should just do precisely what we practiced!)
Tsukasa: (Giving up the spotlight to him might've been a bit of a waste...)
Tsukasa: (But at the end of the day, the show...)
Kijima: You have to find the answer you're looking for on your own.
Tsukasa: (Wait a second... Is that what he meant by that?)
Tsukasa: (I really do have a lot left to learn as an actor...)
Tsukasa: (In order to put on the best performances imaginable, actors have to constantly give their all...)
Tsukasa: (They'd all be laughing at me right now if they were here.)
Tsukasa: (Speaking of which, Emu said that she wanted to throw a farewell party for Rui and me since we'll be leaving the country soon...)
Tsukasa: ...
Tsukasa: (What would they say if they happened to be here to see today's show...?)
Tsukasa: (Emu would probably say, “It was so ridiculously amazingly explosively fun☆”. Nene would likely point out all the little mistakes in my movements.)
Tsukasa: (And I imagine Rui would start coming up with a directing plan that includes a number of extra effects.)
Tsukasa: (In any case, I would've been told I'm a fledgling with a lot left to learn.)
Tsukasa: (I have to keep finding ways to grow...)
Tsukasa: (As the troupe leader of Wonderlands×Showtime, I can't let them hog all the glory.)
